Peter Collingwood https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Peter_Collingwood 0 Peter Trevor Collingwood (6 May 1920 – 23 September 2016) was an English-born actor who appeared on stage in England and Australia, as well as being a theatre writer, and in a number of British and Australian films, miniseries and serials from 1938 to 2003. Known for his portrayal of judges, military men, and upper-crust, befuddled types.
